BodyTogh.whatisToghExample.defaultMessage: Potluck with the school? Barbecue with Friends? Road trip with Family on m? multiple days? This is an event.

BodyTogh.whatisToghExplanation.defaultMessage: Togh is an application to manage your event.

BodyTogh.whatisToghPossibility.defaultMessage: In one event, organize participants, register tasks and shopping list, give address, specify steps your road trip. You can ask the participant any survey: do they prefer to visit Hollywood Bld, or the Griffith Observatory (Paul want to visit both!) Visualize the itinerary on the map. Calculate expense. Togh will tell who owns who.

BodyTogh.whyToghBorn.defaultMessage: Here Togh was born. I was thinking of this application for five years now.

BodyTogh.whyToghConclusion.defaultMessage: So this application was really needed at this moment.

BodyTogh.whyToghHistory.defaultMessage: Last year, when I organized a road trip for my family (which was canceled, due the Covid), I had to use Furkot to build the itinerary, make Doogle for the survey, opening a Splitwise to share the expense, a Google Doc to describe the itinerary, Facebook group to exchange idea.

BodyTogh.whyToghMotivation.defaultMessage: I wanted to learn React, Spring. Plus, I wanted to put my hand in the Cloud deployment. So, why not build an application using all these technologies, and see what's going on?

Event.TourNameContent.defaultMessage:
This name must be explicit. It will be used in Email, visible by participants.
You can reuse the same name.
Example: 'Party at San Marbella', 'House coming'

Event.TourScopeContent.defaultMessage:
The scope determines who can see and search the event.
  • Open: everybody can search and join the event.
  • Open on confirmation: anybody can search, ask to join. Then, an organizer must validate the person.
  • Limited:Only invited person can access it
  • Secret: share a number. The only person with this number can join, and participants are hidden from each other.

Event.TourScopeNote.defaultMessage: Only an organizer can change the scope

Event.TourStatusContent.defaultMessage:
The status event change: at the beginning, it will be in preparation, active. After the event, the status is done
You can change the status manually, but keep in mind Togh will move it automatically to Active when it will start, and done after the end of the event
